  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (coverage gap adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results span the nominal operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM); edge cases including minimum-flow near-stall conditions (< 1 L/min) and maximum-speed high-shear-stress regions (> 4000 RPM) were studied in companion work and are not linked here.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
