      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; selection of SST k-omega turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating machinery flows. Modified power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) documented with literature references. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; nominal input values documented with sources.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients sourced from published literature and manufacturer specifications. Nominal values documented in simulation report. Formal sensitivity analysis of model inputs not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least 3 independent experimental replicates per operating point to characterize measurement variability; coefficient of variation < 10% for RH measurements.",
      "rationale": "Three independent experimental runs performed at each of the five nominal operating points (n=15 total). Coefficient of variation for RH measurements ranges from 2.1% to 6.8% across operating points, all below the 10% threshold. Measurement uncertainty quantified per ASME PTC 19.1. Gradation 2 achieved. Note: test samples do not include specimens tested at near-stall or high-speed extreme conditions specified in the COU intendedUse; those samples are documented in a companion study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
